  "prompt": "What is the meaning of tax rebate? As per the year budget, tax rebate is now 5000 for salary more than 5 lakh. What does it mean in a lay man language?",
  "response": "In simple terms, a tax rebate is a refund or reduction in the amount of taxes you owe. It usually means that after calculating your total tax liability, you can reduce it by the rebate amount.\n\nIn the context of your example, if the budget specifies that there is a tax rebate of 5000 for individuals with a salary of more than 5 lakh, it means that if you earn more than 5 lakh, you are eligible to reduce your total tax bill by 5000. \n\nFor instance, if your calculated tax amount for the year is 20,000, you would apply the rebate and only need to pay 15,000 (20,000 - 5,000). Essentially, it\u2019s a way to give taxpayers some financial relief by lowering their tax payments.",
